DataElement.preferredName: Peptide Hit Last Amino Acid java.lang.String
DataElement.preferredDefinition: A compound of two or more amino acids where the alpha carboxyl group of one is bound to the alpha amino group of another. Peptides are smaller than proteins and the dividing line is around 50 amino acids.:A positive return on a search in a database or by way of a search engine on the Internet; the request for and delivery of a file (such as a Web page) on a server._Coming after all others in time or space or degree or being the only one remaining.:Organic compounds containing amino (-NH2) and carboxyl (-COOH) groups.  In biochemistry, used to refer to the twenty-plus L-alpha-amino acids found in proteins._Generic value domain for a java datatype that is a class that represents character strings.
